 Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"l'Orti","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Benedetto, Guido, Luigi.","Italian: nickname from <i>torto</i> ‘twisted, tortured, sullen’ and also ‘odd’, ‘strange’ from Latin <i>tortus</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry de l'Orti was born in 1255, in Axford, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Henry Lorty Of Axford, was 21 and his mother, Mrs. Henry Lorty, was 18. He married Mrs Henry de l'Orti about 1274. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1342, at the age of 87."},"et":{"1255–1342":"1255–1342","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1257–Female":"1257–Surnud","1277–1295":"1277–1295","1235–1321":"1235–1321","1237–Female":"1237–Surnud","Abt 1274":"umbes 1274","BEF 1295":"enne 1295","1237":"1237","1235":"1235","1257":"1257","1255":"1255","1321":"1321","1277":"1277","1342":"1342","about 1277":"umbes 1277","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","Axford, Wiltshire, England":"Axford, Wiltshire, England","Axford,Wiltshire,England":"Axford, Wiltshi